What the contract does:
The contract collects the users' funds through allocate. It returned the funds to the allocators viafunction allocate.
The vulnerability:
It also had an onlyOwner function collectAllocations through which the owner could collect all the funds.
How I exploited it:
The vulnerability was that the owner was to be set in the supposed constructor. But the constructor name had a typo because of which it didn't become a constructor and anyone could call it at any time. I became the owner from there and drained the funds.
Prevention:
Always make sure that the constructor name is the same as the contract name and avoid putting privileges in functions without access control.
